name: Version 2.3.0
body:
- Deprecated a bunch of properties I wanted to nuke (don't say I didn't warn you this was coming!)
- Refactored deprecated video player code
- General cleanup

name: Version 2.2.1
body:
- Addresses some deprecation issues
- Minimum deployment target is now iOS 8.0
- General code cleanup

name: Version 2.2.0
body:
The following changes were done for my personal sanity, as I was never really happy with the architecture of this from the start:
- Refactored a good deal of the internals to fix issues with the view controller life cycle
- Exposed the main UI elements, rather than individual properties for each element, allowing for more explicit customization and less forcing of design styles by the framework
- Deprecated the custom styling properties and the convenience methods to set them globally. These deprecated methods will be removed in the next release (v3.0.0) to keep everything as tidy as possible because I'm slightly OCD.

name: Version 2.1.8
body: Small release to push out some of the newest pull requests live via CocoaPods.

name: Version 2.1.7
body: Added the `fadeSkipButtonOnLastPage` property to address the feature request here https://github.com/mamaral/Onboard/pull/82.

name: Version 2.1.6
body: Minor version update after major repo reorganization.

name: Version 2.1.4
body: Fixes what appears to be a UIKit bug, where showing a `UIAlertView` during a page view controller transition causes a crash.

name: Version 2.1.2
body: Bug fixes and exposing of a few properties for customization.

name: Version 2.0
body:
- Introduced new background video feature, allowing you to loop local video files in the background rather than static images.
- Added new customization, including disabling swiping, auto-navigation, and hiding page control.
- Added new convenience initializers.
- Code and project formatting improvements.
